getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleGranted} event.

params.buyerReasoning: The reasoning of the buyer in favor of the claim
params.itemId: The ID of the item involved in the dispute
params.sellerReasoning: The reasoning of the seller against the claim

params.addrNewShop: The address of the new Shop contract proposed

params.disputeId: The ID of the target dispute
The ID of the target dispute

params.upgradeProposalId: The ID of the target proposal
The ID of the target proposal

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been revoked `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `callerConfirmation`. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

params.proposalId: The ID of the upgrade proposal

params.disputeId: The ID of the target dispute
params.secret: The secret used to commit the vote

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

CONTROL_ROLE().notice: The Control role ID for the AccessControl contract. At first it's the msg.sender and then the shop.

DEFAULT_DISPUTE_QUORUM().notice: The default number of voters for passing a dispute vote

DEFAULT_PROPOSAL_QUORUM().notice: The default number of voters for passing an update vote

PROPOSAL_EXECUTION_DELAY().notice: The minimum waiting time between approval and execution of a proposal

PROPOSAL_REVIEW_TIME().notice: The time window in which a proposal can not be voted

PROPOSAL_VOTING_TIME().notice: The minimum voting period for a proposal

THRESHOLD().notice: The threshold for the random number generator

cancelDispute(uint256).notice: Cancel an ongoing dispute. Either by the buyer or blacklisting (shop contract)

cancelProposal(uint256,string).notice: Cancel an ongoing upgrade proposal by the admin of the DAO (who knows the password)

cancelProposalByCreator(uint256).notice: Cancel an ongoing upgrade proposal by the proposal creator

castVoteOnProposal(uint256,bool).notice: Cast a vote on an upgrade proposal

checkLottery(uint256).notice: Randomly award an NFT to a user if they voten for the winning side

commitVoteOnDispute(uint256,bytes32).notice: Commit the hash of the vote

disputeQuorum().notice: Min number of people to pass a dispute

endDispute(uint256).notice: Resolve a dispute if MIN_REVEALING_TIME has elapsed and if enough users have voted or MAX_REVEALING_TIME has elapsed. Then remove it from the storage

nextDisputeId().notice: The ID of the next dispute to be created

nextUpgradeProposalId().notice: The ID of the next upgrade proposal to be created

proposalQuorum().notice: Min number of people to pass a proposal

queryDispute(uint256).notice: Query the details of a dispute

queryDisputeResult(uint256).notice: Query the result of a dispute

queryUpgradeProposal(uint256).notice: Query the details of an upgrade proposal

queryUpgradeProposalResult(uint256).notice: Query the result of an upgrade proposal

resolveUpgradeProposal(uint256).notice: Resolve a proposal if enough users have voted and enough time has passed

revealDisputeVote(uint256,bool,string).notice: Reveal a vote on a dispute if commiting time has elapsed

setShop(address).notice: Sets the shop address as the new Control role

shopAddress().notice: The address of the Shop contract

upgradeProposals(uint256).notice: Current upgrade proposals, indexed by upgradeProposalId
